humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the report, there are metastases carcinomatosae in 2 out of 43 assessed axillary lymph nodes (No II/XLIII). This corresponds to N1 stage as per the AJCC staging system (New Rule 12: N1 indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes).

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report mentions 'Metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis axillae (No II/XLIII)'. This indicates that there are cancer metastases in axillary lymph nodes and that out of 43 lymph nodes examined, 2 of them contain metastases. This corresponds to an N1a stage.
